---

FINAL THOUGHTS

This year has been challenging and rewarding. Every day is different. Every kid is different. The plan guides me but I have to stay flexible and respond to what kids actually need, not what I think they should need.

That's Montessori - follow the child. Sometimes that means throwing out your beautiful plan and going in a completely different direction.

But having this framework helps. Knowing where we're heading, what materials come next, what skills we're building. The map isn't the territory but it helps you navigate.

Year's not over yet (writing this in February) but I'm proud of what we've accomplished so far. These kids have grown. As a teacher, so have I.

